:INFO
The Political Fantasy That Got Everything Right
A Memory Called Empire is a debut novel about an ambassador named Mahit Dzmare \
who arrives at the capital of a vast empire to discover that her predecessor is \
dead and no one will tell her how. Arkady Martine manages to make trade \
negotiations and poetry recitation feel genuinely thrilling. The novel is also \
about what it feels like to love a culture that does not fully accept you, which \
is a political idea that most fantasy novels only gesture at from a distance.

:NOW
Reading the sequel and finding it holds up to this one

:QUOTE [subtitle:Arkady Martine, quotetype:PLAIN]
Three percent of her was afraid, and she was paying attention to the three percent.

